HEADWORD: Mesosternum
<hw>Mes`o*ster"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> + <ets>sternum</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The middle portion, or body, of
the sternum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The ventral piece of the middle
segment of the thorax in insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mesotartaric</ent>⟦br⟧
